Great prices with great location, close to metro, and some useful buses. Most central attractions were close. A lot of restaurants and shops a 5 minute walk away.

Staff was the highlight. Friendly and helpful, always available.

The rooms aren't flashy, and some things creak a bit. However, everything was very clean, and we had all amenities we could want from a hotel in 2025.

I recently had the pleasure of staying at London Lodge with my daughter for 11 nights and it was an absolutely delightful experience from start to finish! The room was incredibly comfortable and clean and the wifi was fast, etc.

The service at the hotel was truly impeccable. Every member of staff, from the reception team to the F&B staff, was polite, friendly, and went above and beyond to ensure that our needs were met. They were always happy to assist with any queries or requests we had.

The breakfast was a highlight of our stay - delicious and freshly prepared. We looked forward to it every morning!

The hotel's location was also a major plus, with convenient access to the tube and bus stops, making it easy to get around. There were also plenty of amenities nearby and a variety of dining options to choose from such as Thai, Pubs, Italian, etc.

What really made our stay stand out, however, was the personal touch from Mandy. She regularly checked in on us, making friendly conversation, and ensuring that we felt welcomed and at home. This is a service you don't see often anymore in many other hotels.

Overall, I would highly recommend London Lodge Hotel to anyone looking for a comfortable, convenient, and welcoming place to stay. We felt safe, relaxed, and thoroughly enjoyed our time here. Thank you to the entire team for a wonderful stay - we can't wait to come back!

We recently stayed here for one night and had a home from home experience, using the last-minute discount. Staff were very friendly, helpful and available. The hotel is on a quiet street, so we had a good sleep. We stayed in a triple at the back of the hotel, which was nice and quiet. Whilst the room was a bit dated, it was clean and everything worked. Could do with some sockets near the bedside tables (for mobile charging). We had a lovely breakfast the next morning, both continental and full english are tasty. We would come here again !

A wonderful, comfortable, homey, incredibly well-situated hotel. I greatly enjoyed my short stay. The decor reminded me of my late mom’s style—influenced by our time living in London. The breakfast was delightful and they were easily able to accommodate my gluten free breakfast request. I appreciated that the owner was present and engaged in warm conversation between me and other guests. And wow, just a short walk away from Holland Park. Absolutely lovely!

editorial_summary.overview: 52-seat independent cinema with cafe bar, showing arthouse, classic and indie films.

reviews.text:
Just went here for the first time and I'm absolutely in love with this place. Immaculate vibes, delicious cocktails, great music, wonderful staff, comfy seats in the bar and cinema, cheap popcorn...

They're showing all sorts of queer movies. Its literally the perfect place if you just want to hang out at the bar or watch a film or both!

A great place to work, read, chill in SE1. I love the business model, education, awareness, art, the cinema, subscription, discounts. It’s got a great vibe, nice books too on queer and art, politics, critical theory and very multipurpose without being preachy. They’ve kept the menu light which is great. They do coffees with biscuits and their mocktails are some of the best I’ve had! Would choose the virgin over their happy hour booze though - but very generous. Love these guys anyway - good vibes & a lot of intention behind it all. Also adding with all the listening bars buzz going on in the city: a fantastic playlist, the films are chosen so well - everything has a soul and mind behind it - keep it up!
Haven’t tried the cinema yet, but the bar part is excellent! A hidden gem just off bermondsey street. Fantastic cocktails and great vibe. Highly recommend

Had I not been staying in the hotel next door last night I would never have the pleasure of discovering this hidden gem! Nestled next to the Bermondsey Square Hotel this newly opened bar (and soon to be opened cinema) is well worth a visit. The staff are lovely and the food snacks & drinks menu are on point. Our order of Rhubarb Gin & Tonics and Mushroom Rolls were delicious! We will definitely be back

Great place! So happy to have a LGTBQ+ space in the area (I would say the Q are very important). Super kind staff. Cocktails are really good (they know what they are doing). A bit expensive, but they are very good and there is a happy hour from 4 to 6pm. It was a cinema. Not sure if movies are playing.

editorial_summary.overview: Tradtional pub with craft ales, serving pints to politicians from the Houses of Parliament opposite.

reviews.text:
Our second time here over 9 year period as a tourist, and it’s still a great place. It was even recommended by British friends as a must visit place when dropping into London.
Nothing beats sitting in their outside seatings looking at the parliament view. The beer and fish and chips were well worth it. Very friendly bartenders.

Delicious fish and chips, the fish smelled of the sea. Customer focus 10+. Bahman welcomed us with extreme kindness and made us sit right away. He also recommended some delicious beers, we will definitely be back!

A typical English pub in the center of London under Big Ben, serving delicious fish at a much higher price than anywhere else, but in this place with such a great atmosphere, it's worth it and incredibly enjoyable. The waiters are attentive, the fish is delicious, the tartar sauce is wonderful, and our bellies are full, satisfied, and happy. Recommended!!!

The atmosphere is pure British. They have nice fish and chips, I found that it was perfectly buttered for me. The food came out quite fast, despite there were many people here.

The Tavern is located right in front of Big Ben, which is really good. However, most of the visitors are tourists, same as I and I didn't find many British people here.

I spent around 20£ on fish&chips and about 8£ on Stella, which is quite cheap in this busy area.

Minuses: I didn't find a place to put my coat, same as the table next to me. And I couldn't put it on a stool as well.
Popped in here after a nice walk around London. It was fabulous. Alex had the fish and chips I had the vegetable curry. Absolutely delicious

editorial_summary.overview: English and American breakfasts, plus comfort foods and burgers in cheerful, quirky surrounds.

reviews.text: This place was highly recommended by my cousin because of the eggs. The actual location is really cute. The staff is super friendly. The food took forever. I ordered the eggs with bacon and a milkshake. My husband ate as well and was totally fine but for me the wait for the food was too long.

Nice, simple dishes with fast service. The space is cute and perfect for a quick lunch or brunch. One of the servers was really nice and smiling, but the other was less welcoming, which unfortunately brought down the overall experience.

We arrived half an hour before our reservation and were seated immediately! The restaurant had a warm and inviting atmosphere, complemented by friendly staff.

The menu offered so many tempting options that it was hard to decide, but we eventually opted for classic breakfast dishes.

The portions were generous, especially for the price. We also appreciate that they leave a  jug of water at our table, eliminating the need to constantly ask for refills.

Lovely cafe with a great atmosphere. I only ordered a hot chocolate but their menu was comprehensive and offered a good variety. Plus, the food everyone else was having looked amazing. Good prices too, for the location. Would definitely come again! 🤩

Hello, it was the 24th, if we need to buy the last 🎁 gifts for Christmas... but first a stop for a coffee, yes we have looked at different locations, there are many for a coffee in Angel station. But we decided to enter The Breakfast Club. It was very busy, we decided to wait. It was for a coffee and we looked at the menu and everything seemed very tempting, we really like avocado and we ordered everything with avocado and pancakes. The coffees were incredible, we even asked where the delicious coffee came from and it wasn't that the friendly and kind Mateo who served us commented that it came from my country Brazil 🇧🇷, how nice... We recommend 💯 x 💯 this place, if you fancy fresh, good, fast and with kind attention. Thank you Mateo, for your wonderful work👏👏, and thanks to the entire team for a job well done🙏👍. We recommend and we return yessss. Happy Christmas and beautiful 2025 to all 💖🙏

editorial_summary.overview: Traditional pub with chunky tables and bright sofas, open all day for breakfast, lunch and dinner.

reviews.text:
★★★★★

Visited Somers Town Coffee House for a business lunch with colleagues, and it was an excellent experience. The atmosphere was amazing, warm, inviting, and beautifully decorated. The staff were outstanding, super attentive, professional, on point from, and the food was absolutely brilliant. We all went for the burger, and it was cooked to perfection, juicy, flavorful, and just epic. Highly recommended for both business and social gatherings. Will definitely be back!

Great place for breakfast!
The owner is really nice and took our picture... and added a joke.
We highly recommend this place :)

Very costly food for a pub for half portion size. Took 30+ min for olives and a basque cheesecake to come even though the pub was empty. The heaters don’t work the choice of drinks are also limited. The washroom stank of piss. The compote on the cheesecake was watery. The buns of the burger was burnt. The olives were very salty.

Had a yummy veggie brunch and cappuccino here today! Brilliant location near King’s Cross Station. Lovely interior and spacious. Friendly and efficient service - they even swapped my plate and put the hollandaise sauce on the side when I requested less. Look forward to visiting again!

We had a lovely time here. Came on a Friday evening. The food is above average for a pub, it wasn’t too hectic and busy, and the waiter/manager was super friendly. I can see other reviews saying it’s a bit expensive for what you get but everywhere is like that at the moment. Nice place off the beaten track. Close to King’s Cross and the British library (worth a visit).

editorial_summary.overview: Industrial chic decor, an upbeat vibe & eclectic global cooking served all day in a hip hub.

reviews.text:
When you’re paying 70 quid for breakfast for 2, the minimum I expect is for it to arrive hot. Additionally, when you’re paying three quid for a side of sourdough toast, I don’t expect to be charged £1 extra for the privilege of being able to butter said toast!

To be fair to them, when the food came the second time it was hot, tasted great and the waiting staff were apologetic, so all good in the end.

You have a great place with great food and a nice vibe going on. Of course you have to pay for quality no problem with that - but charging a quid for butter is a total rip-off and blatant profiteering which even the waitress said she was embarrassed about! Sort it out guys!

It was sub-par compared to other branches. For example, we asked for strawberry on top of the porridge, which was an add-on for £2.5. It was forgotten at first and then there was literally one strawberry cut in three. It was unacceptable.

There were almost no plant-based options for those who were vegan in our group. Disappointing.
Charming place with great and friendly service. We had a chance to enjoy breakfast in this restaurant and everything was delicious.

Beautiful and clean place.
Nicely decorated. Service was good.
But food and coffee is below average and little pricy.
The food is really healthy and delicious. They have a bar where you can ask for different kind of cocktail. I really enjoy the place but could be very busy but the wait worth it.

editorial_summary.overview: Bohemian industrial cafe with all-day menu and takeaway snacks, plus evening DJs and live acts.

reviews.text: Came on a Tuesday which was a bring your own vinyl night, such a great incentive for people to branch out their music taste with the wide variety of genres that will play. Everyone here is very friendly which is even more welcoming, a very nice atmosphere to sit and chat with friends. Ordered a coffee which was a little bit on the bitter side but the music made up for it! A great evening out, will definitely make this a regular spot to kick back

The atmosphere of the place is incredible. It can get crowded but you should definitely go. We stayed there with friends for coffee but you can also get food and even cocktails in the evening. The decoration is superb and it’s a very cool place in general. I will come back !!

I just happened upon this place on my way to Rough Trade records. Cafe 1001, it's a very cool place to have a bite and they have really cool stereo place upstairs food is great service is great what can I say it's a great place!

My Wife and me were in London for a couple of nights .  We were staying very near to Brick Lane.  We discovered Cafe 1001 today when we were looking for a place to have breakfast.  What an amazing place.  The food the atmosphere the staff the sounds.  Don’t pass this place by.  Chilled friendly atmosphere with great food and such good energy.  Craig and Christina from Scotland.  We’ll be back !!

Great experience overall - service was great and the food was really good in general.
The steamed milk on my cappuccino wasn’t great, and the toilets aren’t pleasant.
The music was super nice and created a good atmosphere - it was a bit too loud in the beginning, but ended up being fine.

Wish I could rate 4 stars, as the stuff mentioned is easily fixable and the atmosphere is super nice with sweet staff

editorial_summary.overview: Modern Italian venue on 3 floors with deli/cafe, bar and monochrome dining room with giant windows.

reviews.text:
The food is delicious and the potions sizes are decent. But please keep in mind that the menu is not very long, for example the options of pasta are limited.
P.S. Service charges and "optional donations" are getting out of hand (not specific to just this place)

I booked a table for 11, for a team dinner. The process was smooth from start to finish and the team were so accommodating and attentive to everything I asked for (square table, allergies, changing numbers last minute etc.).
On the night, the team looked after us quietly but attentively. The food was fresh and well‑cooked, and the wines they suggested paired nicely.
A reliable, easy option for a relaxed team dinner in the City - highly recommended!

Great food, excellent service.
I went on a monday, so it was not busy. Great mussels for the entrée, crab pasta for the main dish and chocolate mousse for dessert. All great options. Also, a short menu ensures all comes out fast and tasting good!

Great food, good service and staff is super attentive. Came here with my work colleagues. The vibe is good, relaxed and chill and they have a good setup. Little tricky to find if you haven’t been here before as the name hides under two massive trees but once you’re in, it’s great. Would highly recommend and definitely visit again.
Good breakfast meeting place in the City. Great service, team friendly and welcoming, good breakfast choices.

editorial_summary.overview: Trendy boutique hotel featuring modern rooms & loft suites, plus dining & a rooftop bar.

reviews.text:
Great location for Bermondsey restaurants and short walk from Borough Market. Dog friendly and quiet hotel with bright and modern bathrooms. Room
Was a bit bland but bed comfy and there’s an Nespresso machine free to use in room. Felt the interior of hotel could do with a refresh. Proves dog bowls and a bed ( for a small
Dog!😂!)   Welcoming on arrival and was a fair price. Recommend

The rooms are spacious and set to a good temperature. The water in the shower was super cold though, even when set to hot. The shower also did not smell fresh. I found two very tiny insects, including a moth and a spider, but those did not cause much annoyance at all.

The service from the staff is excellent - very helpful staff, approachable, and always available when you need them. Good breakfast and a few spots/opportunities to socialise with fellow guests indoors and outdoors.

Nice, reasonably spacious rooms with iron, coffee, tea, water and cookies. The showers were good. We had issues with the phone charging though and the rooms lacked a safe. There were convenient bus connections to the city but the nearest tube was a 15 m walk. Also the price was steep but consistent with London rates generally.

We stayed here for a few days. Rooms are clean. Staff are friendly. Location is great. Only took off a star because the heating in the room wasn’t working properly. They gave us a space heater as well but that only for one spot in the room hot so that wasn’t great either.

Staff is very respectful and polite. They greet you with a warm, welcoming smile each time. I enjoyed the breakfast and ensured I came down on time to have my go at the brickle brackle with beans and fizzy wiggets. I highly recommend this hotel, my husband and I are from Trinidad and Tobago, we stayed here for 5-days and I promise you, we will be back! The morning of our flight we saw a fox outside happily playing with a balled up piece of paper, she was so cute.

name: International Students House
address: 229 Great Portland St, London W1W 5PN, UK

details.formatted_address: 229 Great Portland St, London W1W 5PN, UK
details.name: International Students House

reviews.text:
This was my home for nearly a year in London. It's a privilege to live in such a post code as a student. With Regents Park as our back yard.

It's conviniently located just outside of Great Portland Street underground station and a short walk from Regents Park and Warren Street stations.
There a Tesco express right in front and a Saintsbury a short walk away.

The TTS bar and the cafeteria has tasty budget friendly food. And they have the best fried fish and chips and also the best Hot chocolate in town.

The most special fact about ISH is the friendly supportive staff that makes it a home away from home!!

For the price and location, this is a great option. Stayed in a private room (with attached bathroom) for several nights and couldn’t ask for a better place in London for the budget traveler. Everything you need for a long weekend, even laundry service in the building although it’s a bit complicated. A young crowd, a bar/restaurant inside, and a helpful front desk. Right next to the Great Portland Street Tube station and not too far from the Regent’s Park station (and the actual park). Plus Marylebone is a lovely neighborhood with every amenity you need. Would stay here again. Hard to beat!

As a scholar from Nepal, to stay in the International Students House, London was a dream come true! It's the best student house in London, hands down. From the friendly atmosphere to the top-notch facilities, everything was perfect. It became my home away from home, and I made lifelong friends there.
I stayed here for a semester in 2004. So these photos were taken with a disposable camera. I had a great time at ISH it was a great location, was clean and a nice place to stay.

Just seen the magnificent Grateful Dudes but the sound guy would not be moved on the volume. Far too loud and unnecessarily so. Ears ringing despite wearing earplugs.. Less is more. Be subtle.. Stop making everyone have long term hearing issues.

editorial_summary.overview: Counter-service coffee chain offering hot drinks, iced coolers, sweet snacks and sandwiches.

reviews.text:
One of the best Costa Coffee stores.

Atmosphere: awesome

Customer services : excellent. Staffs are very friendly, helpful and approachable.

You would definitely enjoy sipping your coffee here  while charging your phone or laptop as this place has many sockets around the tables. Also there is wireless charging place while you wait for the coffee to be served .  😍

Its a very nice place to spend your lunch. Staff is very friendly and always happy to help although they are very busy they still manage to deal with everything and make delocious drinks and if theres any mistake with the drink, staff is happy to make new one. Also it has nice and big sitting area indoors and outdoors which is not everyday thing you find. In one word - fantastic 😍💙👌
The service is adeguate, the place a little bit dirty and the atmosphere of the place ok, as there is enough place to sit and stay. The food was good.
it was aight. i dont like the smell of coffee so i felt sick but the costa was relatively clean spacious and cozy
Warm and friendly ambience in this branch.. Great staff very friendly and welcoming..also spacious. Plenty of seating..thoroughly recommended.

editorial_summary.overview: Counter-service coffee chain offering hot drinks, iced coolers, sweet snacks and sandwiches.

reviews.text: A nice and convenient Costa Coffee right across Farrington train station. Very friendly staff, and a good variety of coffee and fast foods. Not big, but it's nice. Here are also power outlet, so you can charge a phone or laptop.

Went in there while waiting for a delayed train to turn up. Shop is right outside Faringdon station so is easily accessible. They had what I wanted and made my coffee quickly and effectively. All tasted good. Staff were polite, knowledgeable and happy to be there.

This is one of the better Costa Coffees. The interior is very modern with comfortable seating, plenty of plug sockets and WiFi. This Costa coffee was clean, including the bathroom, and the coffees prepared here were very nice. Staff were also friendly and made good coffee. Good location, right by the station.

Amazing customer service from the lovely Faria who served me with a smile and was ever so kind.

Big minus however as this Costa does not have WiFi.
Decent place to get some food and a drink

editorial_summary.overview: Casual option offering bright rooms, free WiFi and breakfast, plus dining and an art deco-style bar.

reviews.text:
It's location in Bloomsbury close to multiple tube stations makes it convenient to tour London's main attractions. I have been staying in the bloomsbury area hotels from 90s. Rooms are bit small for family (like most old central London properties) and the hotel can do with some newer update in rooms as hotel is now several decades old. But, hotel is clean otherwise, well maintained and a good value in central London for a comfortable stay for a few days' visit. Beds are comfortable and some rooms had a great  view of tavistock square garden. Rooms do not have US plugs, or a/c ( be mindful if visiting in summer.). Rooms have limited power outlets but adequate to charge devices. A US traveler may need to travel with a UK power adapter.

Breakfast is pretty good with lots of choices, but is same every day with no change. Also, no freshly brewed  coffee in the breakfast, only a coffee "cup" machine. Tons of restaurants nearby including a Tesco to shop minor stuff. The company owns six hotels in the area so you can walk and try breakfast in other places if you don't include breakfast with room. Overall- it is quite good hotel in a very safe area with very helpful staff.

This actually was a very nice hotel in a very good location. It’s kind of a large hotel (300+ rooms) so you don’t get the same feel you get from smaller, family owned hotels, however, the staff are very courteous and professional. The space is always kept clean and well maintained. There are 2 restaurants on site, we tried the Indian one and it was great. The location is ideal, many bus stops and underground stations. It made commuting very easy. Also the neighborhood has many restaurants, coffee shops and grocery stores. Regarding the room it served its purpose and the beds were very comfortable, room service was great too.  An electric kettle with coffee and tea is available. However, there is no AC in this room, which was okay for this visit in April as I could open the windows and get a cool breeze, however, I am not sure about the summer. Also, there is no refrigerator in the room, that made having snacks in the room a bit hard. All in all, I would stay here again simply!

Great location! It is so easy to get to anywhere. The room was better than I expected, very comfy and cozy, in a good size. Clean and tidy bathroom. The carpet looks a bit old but for a short stay I was not too bothered. During my stay there was construction on the road which was a bit annoying and noisy in the morning. However, I would still say Tavistock is a great option and worthy of the money. Great service and nice friendly staff. In addition they use digital check-in, so you could have zero contact with the reception, which was quite smart and impressive!
Clean tidy rooms but a bit basic. Very warm at night because the windows don't open much but kindly provided electric fans in the rooms. Comfy bed. Will definitely stay again. This is my third visit

Location is absolutely great, neighborhood is lovely, several parks nearby.
Liked · Breakfast was superb! Really big selection of food, everything was fresh and tasteful. In rush hours was small queue, but nothing too serious. The staff helped to find the free table so you don't have to worry where to sit. Really comfortable bed and pillows.
Disliked · The interior is little old, but really clean. Shower was leaking little bit, but it worked and there was really hot water, if needed.

name: St James's Café
address: Horse Guards Rd, London SW1A 2BJ, UK

editorial_summary.overview: All-day British cuisine in a contemporary wooden pavilion with terrace and views of St James's Park.

details.formatted_address: Horse Guards Rd, London SW1A 2BJ, UK
details.name: St James's Café

reviews.text: Today me and my friends had a great experience at St Jame’s park Cafe. The staff was really welcoming and smiling while we were ordering. The food was delivered in time and really delicious, i recommend the fish and chips😍. The coffee was well presented and the scone… absolutely delicious.

It sounds like you had a mixed experience at the shop. A 3 for the food due to its difficulty to eat might be a concern if you were looking forward to a comfortable meal. Not knowing if they have a microwave can certainly add to that uncertainty. On top of that, a non-smiling service desk lady might give the impression that the customer service wasn't the best, but it's understandable that she could have been working all day.

On the bright side, giving a 5 for the shop's location in the park suggests that the setting is lovely and enjoyable. It's always nice when a place is situated in a beautiful spot. If you plan to go back, maybe you could ask about the microwave situation or try another dish that might be easier to handle.

The breakfast plate is a hearty and well-balanced English-style spread. Juicy sausages and crispy bacon provide a savory punch, while the fried egg—beautifully done with a bright yolk—adds richness. The grilled tomato and mushroom lend a rustic, earthy touch, complemented by a generous scoop of well-seasoned breakfast potatoes. Baked beans in a small portion offer a sweet contrast without overwhelming the plate.

Highly recommended for those seeking a relaxing breakfast with quality food and a touch of nature.

Lovely ambiance. The at table ordering system was down, but nothing indicated that when we ordered. So after watching 20 people order and get their food and drinks we asked and learned our order had not been received. The mistake was corrected quickly and with apologies. However the eggs Benedict was cold when it came out. It was not even room temperature. They said the ham was supposed to be that way because of the kind of ham it is. Fine. But the eggs and bread were also cold as if they’d sat in a refrigerator. I asked if they could heat it in the microwave and they would not due to the ham. They offered to remake it, but I was too hungry by that point and ate it cold. It was sustenance and that was it. My partner had the English breakfast and it met expectations.

Came with family after experiencing the guard changing ceremony at Buckingham Palace. Got a good seating area, the staff were friendly and the service was great. We ordered fish and chips and it was amazing. Will definitely recommend this place ❤️

name: The Orangery Restaurant
address: Kensington Palace Gardens, London W8 4PX, UK

editorial_summary.overview: Dining room set in a garden pavilion built for Queen Anne in 1704, serving lunches, teas and cakes.

details.formatted_address: Kensington Palace Gardens, London W8 4PX, UK
details.name: The Orangery Restaurant

reviews.text: The food and cocktails were divine from presentation to taste. Our waiter Giorgian was very polite, knowledgeable and extremely kind. He looked after our table making us feel like royalty in every little detail. The Orangery is a magical and historically significant venue. A special thank you to Giorgian. The service was impeccable. And congratulations to the entire staff team. You all made our day so special! Highly recommend.

Although I have been living in Kensington for a while, last Saturday was my first visit to the Orangery Restaurant. I ordered a chocolate fondant that melted in my mouth; it was incredibly delicious, and the presentation on the plate was stunning. A friendly Brazilian waitress served me, which made the experience even better. I will definitely return to try more dishes from the menu, as everything looked fantastic.

I went with my friend to the afternoon tea and it was an unique experience. We reserved a table in front of the window with a view of the garden, perfect. I would like to thank the hostess Nessa who welcomed us and also the dear and attentive waitress Eliana who served us. She recommended the teas to drink and explained to us the whole experience. It was incredible, the environment is impeccable and well lit. I highly recommend it!
We enjoyed the afternoon tea in the park setting. Each item on the three tiers tasted very nice. The tea was also well prepared and delicious.

We’ve spend our last hours of a lovely romantic getaway on the sunny terras of this marvelous place. What an exceptional experience. We felt royal. The food was delicious and the desserts are to die for ! Big compliments to the chef. Special thanks to Eliana one of the lovely staff members who took the time to have a lovely little chat with us. Would 100% recommend this place. Prices good, lovely view, food delicious, quiet, child friendly, smoke free

name: The Wallace
address: Hertford House, Manchester Square, London W1U 3BN, UK

editorial_summary.overview: French brasserie set in the Wallace Collection's glass-roofed courtyard and sculpture garden.

details.formatted_address: Hertford House, Manchester Square, London W1U 3BN, UK
details.name: The Wallace

reviews.text: The service is indeed poor. Dirty pot. Be prepared to wait a long time to be served, served the wrong food, wrong bill, you ask for help and be totally ignored. I am glad to be here alone, no way to come with a guest or for business. Beautifully airy on sunny days but it can get loud even before the lunch time starts. Ofc, overpriced. Plenty of good cafes in the area eg Arome.

We went with a baby about to sleep in a push chair (12:45pm 9th March 2025)The women at the entrance (wore black jacket) offered us a table with very small space around it - with a very arrogant manner. She basically said you can take this table or get out and que. The hospitality wasn’t great and food was over priced for what they were.
It’s very shame because all other staffs at the Wallace Collection were very friendly and lovely.

Beautiful setting, average (to mediocre) afternoon tea.

🫖 went for afternoon tea for a friends birthday. Staff was kind but a bit scattered and not very attentive. The actual food was pretty bad- I found the cheese and chutney sandwich inedible, as well as a food portion of the desserts and they were overly/sickly sweet. I couldn’t eat all of it because it started making me feel sick, and I left a bit hungry. For around £50 (without bubbles), I don’t think this is a great deal. However the setting is beautiful!

The food was lovely, I had a chicken terrine - it had nice texture, taste was pheasant too. The service was very good. The atmosphere was excellent - a bit hot under the glass roof.
Bear in mind menu in a cafe and restaurant  are 1 different things and don't  overlap..

Remember you are in London, with London prices. The service was good, table service. Only wanted a light bite, so had a cream tea. This consisted of 2 small scones, clotted cream and any hot drink on the menu.  I did not feel rushed and enjoyed a relaxing break whilst visiting the museum and accompanying exhibition.
The surprise was a 12.5% service charge. I'm not against a serving charge, just the way it was applied with no choice. This addition could make it clearer.
Would have no hesitation to visit again.

editorial_summary.overview: Counter-service coffee chain offering hot drinks, iced coolers, sweet snacks and sandwiches.

reviews.text: Very friendly staff. Very helpful. Clean bathroom facilities. Peaceful atmosphere.
One of the best sweets i have been tried for is the #MapleHazel Latte. It is very delicious and a lot of Autumn 🍂 flavours with a hint of roasted hazelnut into it😍

Costa is a pleasant coffeeshop. This branch is nicely situated on the main road. And yet it's quiet and peaceful.

I ordered a large latte. It was nicely presented and it had a nice bubbly texture on top. Brown sugar gives it some good sweetness.

This branch is clean and tidy with friendly staff. Nice place.

Not the greatest of skills making requested order and not helped by arguing how a dry cappuccino should be made. At least a more experienced colleague stepped in to take over. But all a bit begrudging and not a great feeling

Standard Costa Coffee situation at this particular branch. The staff, my food and my drink were all fine. The atmosphere felt fairly standard for a coffee shop. Prices are becoming quite high, particularly for the food, so much so that the value feels less and less worth the outing. Nothing exceptional and nothing terrible! 🙌

editorial_summary.overview: Airy industrial bar/restaurant with a smart cocktail lounge and a simple, contemporary British menu.

reviews.text: This is a lovely hangout for avant-garde film and moving picture creatives such as actors and other film experts. Cinemas are amazing inside with super comfortable seatings and proper film buff kind of a feel inside. BFI often shows movies which are impossible to find in regular cinemas and in the mainstream picture houses. In the BFI you also have a very interesting media library, where you can watch movies in your own booth or with another person together. I believe this facility is free, with fair use terms applied to it. The cafe and restaurant is also very nice and has a great atmosphere to it with dimmed down lights.

Don’t expect to grab a coffee after an evening screening - not even Coffee and Cigarettes. The bar is open until 10pm. The very expensive looking coffee machine behind the bar closes 2 hours earlier - for cleaning. There is no explanation for this except this is the instruction of Benugo HQ. Right now there are more staff behind the bar doing not much, than customers. Ditto Balcony Bar. At least the Coffee machine looks clean.

The barman was so rude and had such an arrogant attitude. Will not be spending any more money there!

Such a shame as it’s a lovely venue and I had a wonderful previous experience at the other bar/restaurant overlooking the river.

Lovely spot for a chilled something. Food is ok if somewhat overpriced. Service is quick and polite. The main attraction is the space and setting close to the Southbank. Lighting could be improved for a little more brightness without destroying the atmosphere as it can get quite dark.

my friends and I had a delightful evening at the BFI Bar on 21/01/25. The bartender upstairs on this night around 5:30-8:30 was absolutely impeccable, so accommodating and kind (we wish we got her name for this review). We will 100% be attending once again. Can’t fault the service or recommend the house white enough.

P.S. the padron peppers were perfection on a plate 😋

name: Wetherspoons (Victoria Station)
address: Unit 5 (1st Floor, above WHSmith), Victoria, Bermondsey Exchange, Station Concourse, London SW1V 1JT, UK

editorial_summary.overview: No-frills, modern chain bar serving real ales, wine and coffee, plus English breakfast and pub grub.

details.formatted_address: Unit 5 (1st Floor, above WHSmith), Victoria, Bermondsey Exchange, Station Concourse, London SW1V 1JT, UK
details.name: Wetherspoons (Victoria Station)

html_attributions: 香港人心在日本 and Relax Channel

reviews.text:
Lunch Experience at Wetherspoons

I suggested to my sister and cousin from the States to have lunch at Wetherspoons due to my previous positive experiences there. I ordered sausage, beans, and chips, while my sister chose boneless chicken bites, and my cousin went for a Mediterranean salad. We placed our order at the bar, which included glasses of juice with all three meals.

Shortly after, a bar staff member came to our table with one glass of orange juice, and another glass of orange and lemonade, claiming that we had left them at the bar. When my sister pointed out that he was one orange juice short and that she and her cousin didn’t want ice in their drinks, he insisted there were only two drinks on the order and that we should have mentioned our preference regarding ice at the time of ordering. Despite this, he said he would check the receipt to confirm if all orders included a drink. He returned with the third glass of orange juice and placed it on the table.

Unfortunately, this staff member’s attitude put a damper on what had been a wonderful day. It was my cousin’s first trip to the UK, and this experience did not reflect well on British hospitality.

If it weren't for this staff member's demeanor, I would have given a 5-star rating, as I enjoyed my lunch and had good interactions with the other staff.

My recent visit to this place wasn't the most pleasant one I have had within the franchise, and believe me that I visit one every other week. Let's start with what concerned me the most, and it is that they have a CCTV inside the toilet. For someone  who has a reasonable expectation of privacy, I just hope they have a justification for installing a CCTV inside that room. Secondly, the quality of the food served to us last night not only wasn't fresh enough, but the veggie was tired, the pasta was plain and boring, the pizza was burned, super suit, and the mushrooms were raw. Last and most important, I noticed a female staff looking at a southeastern asian colleague in a very despective, arrogant, and not very friendly way. I am not sure if that was a real situation, but it got me very upset seeing her body language towards him. I'll think it twice before choosing to grab another drink or bite there.

I much prefer the Willow Walk just outside the station but still a reasonable Spoons. Casta and Madge keeping watch on the departure board. About 50p a pint station premium over said Willow Walk. Had an Oakham Jeffrey Hudson bitter at 3.8%  £4.79 but used 50p off CAMRA voucher. Excellent. A Cask Marque pub. Bigger than I remember. Balconies either side give great concourse views. 5 real ales. Escalators take you up above the throng.

I was actually pleasantly surprised at how quiet and clean this Wetherspoons was. We went early on the weekend and there was barely anyone, it was peaceful, it was tidy and the staff was very nice and friendly.
I ordered my veggie breakfast, it came quickly and there's nothing much to say about the food, it was the usual Wetherspoon quality but it was what I needed that day.

A lovely quiet morning arrived very early in London and of course first order of the day, tackle a spoons breakfast. On point and as expected and still reasonably well priced. Unlimited lavazza coffee refills, sausage egg tomatoes mushroom beans mountain of toast - all under £12.
Sercice zippy, atmosphere nice relaxing and quiet. I'd you're stuck in Victoria Station there's not many better options.

editorial_summary.overview: Contemporary hotel with conference rooms, free Wi-Fi, a bar & a fusion restaurant.

reviews.text: The hotel is nice enough on its own. I had a fairly spacious room though it did seem like it needed some updates with some discoloured areas around windows in the bathroom. Breakfast was nice and the crew were very helpful. It's centrally located but because it's so close to the train station and tube you can pretty much hear it all the time.

Overall, I was satisfied with my stay. I secured a Sunday night for eighty-five euros, which was a good deal. The room was satisfactory and clean. There was a slight amount of train noise, but it was not unbearable. The inclusion of light coffee and chocolate drink packets was a pleasant addition.

Pretty average hotel. Rooms aren’t the most spacious. Basic amenities.

Carpets in corridors need a deep clean as they smell like wet dog. Self service check in although lady at reception was helpful and supportive. Close enough to Euston station and St Pancras. Definitely ok for a stop over

The rooms are compact but we needed it only for a night as we had a morning flight. The rooms though compact is very clean and has almost everything you would need. The bathroom is great and has a powerful shower. All in all loved it

Excellent location from Euston Train Station.
Arriving at 9.30pm - no restaurant open or room service, surrounding eateries were limited fast food or Indian curry houses. All closed around 10-10.30pm
Room very basic as is clearly Eco friendly & do not count on a good sleep the tube/trains are very loud & regular throughout the night - I was with work colleagues for an event- I will not be staying again

editorial_summary.overview: Counter-service coffee chain offering hot drinks, iced coolers, sweet snacks and sandwiches.

reviews.text:
Costa Coffee on Wigmore Street is a fantastic spot for a quick coffee break or a relaxed catch-up. The staff here are truly exceptional—always friendly, welcoming, and efficient, making every visit a pleasant experience.

If you’re looking for a great snack, I highly recommend the Heinz Beanz & Cheese Toastie. Pair it with their Oat Latte, dairy-free alternative.

The café itself is clean, well-maintained, and offers a comfortable seating area, i am always greeted by a team that truly cares about their customers. Highly recommended!

Yesterday, I ordered an almond croissant and a pot of tea for breakfast.  I asked for a croissant to be warmed up as I only like it warm. This wasn't a problem and a few minutes later I received a delectable pastry of a classic croissant filled with the rich, nutty sweetness of almond filling. Originating from France, this pastry is a favorite in bakeries and patisseries worldwide. The result was delicious, a harmonious blend of textures and flavors that make the almond croissant a beloved treat for breakfast or an indulgent snack.

We were craving for something sweet and appealed by the promotion sign of Costa Coffee on the street. The photo on the sign was the Ruby Chocolate & Light Dairy Swirl, which looked amazingly pretty in dreamy pink color.

We did get their Ruby Chocolate drink with less whipped cream to share with two of us as an afternoon dessert. It was really sweet but extremely satisfying. We could barely taste the flavor from ruby chocolate. We will suggest to ask the staff to give an extra straw since the paper straw was easily soaked and getting soft.
Great service and the cinnamon bun was delicious.  Coffee the best as usual

The worst service . The staff were very rude and slow. The Romanian lady was eating while she was doing the coffees and was speaking to us with her mouth full.
Coffee is looking disgusting,you pay almost £5 for what. If you’re having a bad day you don’t need to put it on your customers .
Lack of professionalism!!

name: ODEON Tottenham Court Rd
address: Central Cross, 30 Tottenham Ct Rd, London W1T 1BX, UK

editorial_summary.overview: Chain cinema for a wide range of entertainment, including the latest releases & live event screenings.

details.formatted_address: Central Cross, 30 Tottenham Ct Rd, London W1T 1BX, UK
details.name: ODEON Tottenham Court Rd

reviews.text: Went to see TXT’s VR concert 3 times and honestly I’ve had the best experience each time! Want to give a shoutout to both Kris and Dami for being so helpful throughout the entire process. Even as I’ve worn the headset and going through the calibrations, I could also hear in the background of them helping every single person who needed help and made sure everyone is comfortable especially when everyone has their gear on and they will make sure that we can see well! They were also super kind enough to let us trade our pcs to our desired members and versions as well. They’re the most kindest and friendliest staff I’ve met! A 5 star rating isn’t enough for their exceptional service. I definitely would give them 10 stars if I could!

This was my first and definitely last visit to Odeon Tottenham court Cinema. I’m absolutely disappointed with the level of service. The staff are not loyal to customers, show zero respect, and have no interest in actually solving problems.

There were plenty of staff around — but none could help. One person couldn’t resolve the issue, so they called someone else, and that person gave the same useless response. It was just a cycle of passing the problem around without taking any responsibility.

I’m a regular customer at other cinemas and I know what good service looks like. This was the complete opposite: disorganized, unprofessional, and totally indifferent to customers.

I ended up waiting for a “solution” that never came, and had to leave before the movie even started. The refund process at the counter was a headache — slow, confusing, and handled with clear reluctance.

Odeon — never again. First and last time.

Not a cinema to return to. In screen 1, found the cinema to be very light, not sure if someone forgot to turn lights off. Screening was continuously disrupted by the entrance door being stuck open when people went to the toilet so that me and a few others ended up having to take turns to shut the door to not have foyer light and noise coming directly into the cinema.

Did raise this with Odeon who's responses boiled down to 'you could have asked for a refund at the time'. The issue is, that's not practical as I don't want to leave part way through a movie and it's not like my time or travel costs would be refunded in that scenario. Poor cinema and poor complaints response from Odeon.

The air conditioning in Screen 2 was extremely loud, making it difficult to focus on the film. I left the screen to speak with a staff member, who said they could turn it off but only temporarily, in case someone else complained about the temperature. I returned to my seat, and the AC turned off briefly, then came back on within a minute. I went back to reception and requested a refund, which was given silently with no apology or even a basic acknowledgment of the issue I had raised. Very disappointing experience, both in terms of comfort and customer service. The purpose of a cinema is to present films well, a quiet screen is fundamentals and should be the minimum expected as an experience being provided.

I visited tonight even after reading the one and two stars views.   The movie was in screen 3.

I have no idea what the other reviewers were talking about.  The staff at the entrance and the guy on the tickets/shop were very friendly and chatty.  The theather itself was clean, the seats were comfy, and there was loads of leg room.

I recommend it.

editorial_summary.overview: Chain cinema for a wide range of entertainment, including the latest releases & live event screenings.

reviews.text:
Great experience.
Wasn’t to busy.
It took a few minutes to order some popcorn and it was ready very quickly.
The theatres are big and specious as well as the screens.
Totally would recommend it going alone, on a date or a group 🍿🎥

Won’t lie there could be some cosmetic improvement but the ticket price and access here is fabulous from my experience. I used it while my daughter was at a gig locally so looked for something to do and with there being a lift with level access seats I was very happy.

It was a maze to find the screen and there wasn't proper signage on the doors to the screens. They also left the lights on for the entire film and didn't do any proper checks. Definitely not going to this one again

Have been here multiple times. It’s fine. The volume could be 25% higher and the lights are always partially left on- could easily read a book in that lighting. Again it’s fine but the light thing is bothersome. The screen was also kind of dirty or there was some sort of issue with the projection? Good prices though.
I always enjoy coming here. There can be technical issues sometimes but everyone's really nice.

editorial_summary.overview: Seattle-based coffeehouse chain known for its signature roasts, light bites and WiFi availability.

reviews.text:
If you come to this franchise it would be you WORST experience of starbucks
The toilet is broke even because i have special condition they didn't let me use the staff toilet,
In the middle of winter they don't allowed people to shut the door!
Nightmare !!!

Inconspicuous Starbucks located across from County Hall, a few steps from the London Eye and close(ish) to Waterloo Station. The location is in a peaceful corner of what is a hectic area of London, and will suit tourists looking to hit the Eye, South Bank, or Westminster across the bridge.

Standard Starbucks offerings inside. My pumpkin spiced latte was made well, but it’s my first time ordering a pumpkin spiced anything and it will certainly be my last… hey, you have to try things at least once, right?  Service was swift; there were quite a few people in front of us, but we were escorted around a couple of people semi-queuing/looking at what to eat, and at least two people were serving and two others making drinks.

This Starbucks used to have more seating inside but in fairness, it created a dingy and cramped atmosphere.  It benefitted from a refit a few months back and now has a more open and friendly feeling about it, with a large counter and plenty of space to move.  There is still some seating outside, some of which is undercover.

As a girl who loves to go Starbucks religiously I was so appalled by this particular bucks. When arriving I immediately made my way to the toilet before ordering, when entering the toilet I was shocked by how absolutely disgusting it was/is. It honestly looked like someone had not cleaned it in like 10 years (Okay not that long, maybe like 5yrs but take my word for it- don’t go in there). After deciding NOT to go into the toilet I decided to order. When ordering I asked for my usual drink and made sure to make it a large as I had enough points to get it for free. The woman didn’t really read it back to me like they usually do at most stores but that wasn’t a problem for me at the time. They called out my name for me to collect my drink and realised that the drink was not filled all the way to the top and was not a large. I can vouch that I’m a very kind person and would never treat anyone rudely so I kindly tried to talk to one of the staff members but no one was open to listening. After finally catching their attention I asked in question if I ordered a large and the barista rudely took my drink and chucked it in the sink and made me a new one. If I’m being so real I wouldn’t be surprised if he spat in my drink from the frustration of making a new drink  lol. The staff need some training on how to talk nicely to people and at least need to look like they know what there doing because you could honestly put 3 kids behind there and they could be kinder and better at the job. Look, I never write reviews believe me ask my past self she would say ‘Hell no, no point’ but this made me upset so I had to write one. I say fix your staff, get your attitude in check, get a cleaner and you got yourself an actual Starbucks because I don’t know what that was.

I visited this Starbucks yesterday and was taken aback by an incredibly unprofessional and disrespectful response from the person at the counter. I offered to pay for my brother’s drinks, which is a common and kind gesture in many cultures, but the staff member called it “annoying.” It’s frustrating to be met with such judgment, especially when it's simply a gesture of courtesy. While I understand that not everyone may be familiar with certain customs, it's disappointing to be treated this way. Basic kindness and respect should always be the expectation, regardless of personal experiences or cultural differences.

Simple drink couldn’t make it right! Please be advised for asian guy barista to double check order all the time. It wasn’t busy and there is no queue I would understand if there is a lot of customer. It was just waste of money.

editorial_summary.overview: Upscale bakery with Parisian origins, specializing in French macarons in a number of flavors.

html_attributions: Carl Astrobix Impianti a fune e videogiochi

reviews.text: I received exceptionally good customer service from three of its staff and wanted to leave a tip. But they told me customers are not allowed to tip the staff and in fact, even if they add tip to the PDQ machine, the staff never receive them. Until you pay your frontline staff as much as you pay your senior managers and CEOs, please let customer tip your staff because they are simply brilliant.

Scones were the best and quite a few items on the menu were unavailable and the afternoon tea came with cheap champagne. Service was poor, and we had to ask several times to order before someone came and one staff was attending to every other table who came after us. On the reservation page  they asked if any special occasions were being celebrated and even had option to upload picture of ourselves so they could greet us. But nothing was arranged and none of the staff looked like they want to be there, much less be welcoming to the customers. However, the view and atmosphere was great and it was a sunny day which made up for the poor service experience.

There are space for dining in the 1st floor and is not wheelchair friendly. We initially asked if there was space to the staff in the shop and they told us to go check ourselves.

The space is tiny, we only were there for tea, so we do not recommned it for a party >4 people. Aside from the macaroons, there were 4 cake options. I was so happy to see that Marie Antoinette (my fave macaroon flavour) was available as a tea. I ordered it but initially it tasted weird. The water they used tasted like tap, so it was not palatable until it the tea steeped longer, when the water's taste was masked. I do recommend the giant pistachio macaroon.

They have a veranda, but I do not recommend during winter. The servers were friendly upstairs. Either way, I'll stick to just buying the macaroons to go.
Typical La Duree with the nice dessert, waiters are not that hospitable can do much better, next time I visit will try the upper floor. Nice idea of offering covers

We sat outdoors and did enjoy the scenery however I specifically went to Ladurée to test the French toast. As a connoisseur it was not my preferable French toast it was extremely rich and overly sweet in taste (not a fan of FT chocolate and vanilla) and lacked the conventional flavour offered by the traditional French toast (strawberry and berries) with maple syrup and compote which is ones favourite because each flavour compliments one another. However did enjoy the macaroons which is what Ladurée is popular for. I plan on trying the French toast in Ladurée Harrods which I have been informed is much better, so I look forward to trying it and informing you all. The overly indulgent French toast look appealing but don’t seem to impress taste wise, from my experience of being a connoisseur simplicity is best.

editorial_summary.overview: Stylish, colourful dorms and private rooms in a chic lodging offering a hip bar and a cafe.

reviews.text:
Great location, walking distance from king's cross station.
However rooms are not the best. You don't have any day to connect your cellphone next to your bed, you have to do it really far.
And the place seems to be a puzzle, rooms have no logic number and showers are really hard to find.

Had a lovely 2 night stay (25th -26th April) at Generator, London but there was a lapse in communication between SpeedyBooker and the hostel meaning the hostel had no record of my payment which added stress to the stay. The hostel staff were brilliant though and offered a free breakfast as compensation. I can't fault them at all. I just hope this doesn't happen again to anyone.  I'd definitely stay here again, the place had a great atmosphere, is in a great location and is perfect for a cheap place to stay

Good for Young Travelers, But Not Ideal for a Quiet Stay

This hostel is affordable and offers very basic amenities. It’s a great choice for budget travelers who enjoy a lively atmosphere, as it’s popular with teenagers and young backpackers.

The rooms are small and minimally equipped—just a small stool with very little space to sit or store belongings. Some rooms don’t have power outlets by the bed, which makes charging devices inconvenient. Bathrooms lack separation for wet and dry areas, and there’s no hairdryer provided. While there are shared hairdryers in the common bathrooms, the one on my floor was broken. On the plus side, the quality of the toiletries was decent.

The biggest downside is the noise. There are no quiet hours or house rules, so it was very loud the night I stayed. The noise continued until 1 AM, and I couldn’t sleep until 2 AM even with ear buds . If you’re traveling with teenagers or enjoy an energetic environment, this could be a good option. However, if you’re looking for a peaceful and comfortable place to rest, I wouldn’t recommend it.

Had an amazing time here both times I came!! First time the guys in the shuffleboard bar were obnoxiously loud to the point we couldn't hear ourselves, but that isn't really the fault of the hostel. The atmosphere for the Barcelona-Inter match was excellent, and the guy at the reception (didn't catch his name, 20-something black guy with braids) was so friendly and helpful!! I do wish that the doors were a bit thicker becuase I was kept up by loud parties passing my dorm. I know it's a party hostel but I do need to sleep 😓 Still would come back though!

I have stayed here twice in the last couple months, for 3 days each time, and I am very happy with my stay, would repeat. It has an exceptional location, in the center of London, and near of the biggest stations, for a very affordable price. The shared bedrooms are equipped enough to have a comfortable sleep and the roommates I had were all really polite and respectful. The reception staff was also very nice and helpful, and quickly solved any concern I had, especially one called Pablo who helped me through my last check-in and gave me advice for my trip in London.

reviews.text: Costa Coffee at Waterloo Station is a convenient spot for a quick caffeine fix amidst the rush. The service is generally efficient, though queues can be long during peak hours. Their Cinnamon Danish is a standout—flaky, buttery, and perfectly spiced with cinnamon, making it a great companion to a Flat White or Americano. While the seating is limited, it’s a reliable choice for a grab-and-go treat before catching a train.

Popped into Costa around 2 PM on a hot Monday, and it was a pleasant surprise. The place was cool, cozy, and spotless, with plenty of seating.
The friendly staff had a chat while I waited for my tea. One of the best Costas I've visited in London, for sure.
Loads of seating upstairs. Open 24 hours. 3 tills for busy times. I got a delicious Soya hot chocolate. Some seating downstairs. Free WiFi and plug points upstairs. Staff are friendly.

I got a salted caramel frappe 8/10 for taste 7.5/10 for price to portion, 7/10 for cleanness and overall service, vibe is okay also 7/10. Definitely a good place to take a rest from long walk or between traveling

I'm actually surprised to see such a good reviews about the service. Unfortunately, I can not say same. I'm ALWAYS getting Costa! There is all sorts of coffee chain stores in Waterloo, I could easily go to any other, and I think I will. 5 mornings in the week (days vary throughout the week as I work different days), I'm always getting same thing which is double espresso, but I also ask for a cup of hot water, simply because I'm freaking cold. Is it so weird?? Every time I get a look as if I was killing somebody when asking for hot water, they look at me, they look at each other thinking "what the heck that bit** wants" - that's the impression I get every single time and I'm fed up. I won't be going there. I get they are busy early in the morning and that takes extra time (10 seconds from her life they will never get back, oh dear... :/) not to mention that in giving them the empty cup for that bloody water! So it's not that I'm getting things for free (I get that the cups cost money too). I'm not going there ever again. Unless the staff changes their attitude, cause I'm not asking for red carpet rolled out on my way to the till or golden dust on my coffee, but hot water! Cause that just simply keeps me alive when I'm freezing cold early in the morning. Anyways... It's not that I'm not recommending the place, I like costa coffee, but it's just frustrating how they make me feel.
